Anthony GIULIANO, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. COMMERCIAL STEVEDORING COMPANY, Defendant-Appellant; United States Shipping Board Merchant Fleet Corporation, Cosmopolitan Fleet Corporation, and Cosmopolitan Shipping Co., Defendants. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. June 3, 1929. No. 363. Clarence E. Mellen, of New York City (Everett W. Bovard, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Levy & Becker, of New York City (Harold R. Medina and Joseph Levy, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before MANTON, L. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
